{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"46a649e2-5352-4408-8b63-c395f3832477","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py` line 3** — `datetime.now()`\n\n```python\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\n**Issues:**\n\n1. **`datetime.now()` is a hard-coded static call** — impossible to freeze time in tests without patching.\n2. **Missing timezone awareness** — `datetime.now()` returns a naive datetime; Django expects timezone-aware datetimes.\n\n**Recommended fix:** Use Django's `django.utils.timezone.now()` and inject it or access via a module-level reference so tests can use `freezegun` or `unittest.mock.patch`:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThis is the only untestable static call in the project. Want me to apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d69dd224-8565-4ef1-aeaf-16f07ebab606","outputTokens":217,"requestId":"4817:99ACC:38BD75F:3E30556:69FBFE94"},"id":"fa121463-66de-4688-85e2-236e98cc6d2d","timestamp":"2026-05-07T02:53:17.598Z","parentId":"e530378d-cd6c-45b8-aca2-ba9633a2f77e"}
